 some treadmills can be equipped with built-in handgrip sensors to scan your heart rate during the running itself. Additionally, by connecting to the fitness applications and syncing your device with the treadmill, you‚Äôll be able to know your intensity zones and your productivity in each of them. So, you‚Äôll manage to follow your progress throughout each workout.</p><p>When using a treadmill for interval training, by knowing your heart rate data, you‚Äôll be able to switch different intensities to train diverse muscles and improve your general stamina. Besides planning your workout, you‚Äôll get to know your recovery period to develop your running capabilities.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696609615264" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696609615264" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;"><span style="color: rgb(221, 51, 51);">Our expert <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/sergii-putsov" class="" target="_blank">Sergiy Putsov</a> gave us a piece of advice:</span></span><br></span></p><p><span style="font-style: italic;">"<b>When choosing a treadmill, prioritize one that's easy to fold and store. It's a space-saving option that still lets you get your cardio in at home.</b></span><span style="font-style: italic;">"</span></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696609692509" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696609692509" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Apparently, the most important things concerning running machines and their functionality are motor capacity, belt length, and cushioning system that ensure maximum comfort and safety for a user. If you prefer running to jogging, you should consider treadmills with a stronger motor and longer running deck. As usual, such running machines are bulkier and heavier than compact models. However, the latter is weaker since they have a motor with minimal capacity and come with a shorter running surface.</span><br></p><p>For more variety to the home run, you can imitate outdoor training by adjusting the incline, so it‚Äôll feel like you‚Äôre running or walking uphill or flat surface. With the incline function, you‚Äôll be able to activate your leg and glute muscles in different ways.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663340399259" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1663340399259" data-resolution="3000x3000" style="display: block;"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/77003547-e480-49a1-bbc5-a94ee7d88ac9/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/best-treadmill-athlete.jpg" alt="man treadmill cardio workout" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="1000px" data-height="auto" title="man treadmill cardio workout" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510287445" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510287445"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Types of Treadmills</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663340399252" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663340399252" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Fitness equipment is evolving all the time, but something you‚Äôll always see in every gym are treadmills - lots of them. And not all treadmills are created equal. This is a great thing, because their variety makes them even more versatile than they already are.</p><p>Before you choose to invest in a new treadmill, consider the type you want. Let‚Äôs go over them!</p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510303532" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510303532"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Manual</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510247292" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510247292" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>A <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-manual-treadmill" class="" target="_blank">manual treadmill</a> is the simplest among all available equipment and it doesn‚Äôt need electricity to operate. It starts to move as you start walking or running by moving the belt. That means that you generate the power to keep a treadmill belt moving. On one hand, it seems too primitive, but on the other hand, a manual treadmill can give you better training than a motorized model. The reason is that your feet move the treadmill belt and it‚Äôs based on the effort you put to propel it, so you do more work and have greater chances to burn more calories.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510320285" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510320285"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Curved</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681942903400" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681942903400" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Almost similar to the previous type, a curved treadmill is self-powered and requires no electricity. However, the belt can move faster compared to the one of the manual treadmill which makes this model better for more speedy running. Some runners say that this type of treadmill brings a natural-like feeling while running. The reason is its curving shape: the higher you step the curve, the faster the belt will move. A curved treadmill can be a good option to train and master your cadence.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1679818941834" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1679818941834" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/b931ac88-600b-46fd-be13-d36b7d333226/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/treadmill-gym-run.jpg" alt="treadmill gym run" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="treadmill gym run" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510330304" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510330304"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Motorized</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681942927200" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681942927200" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>These are the most popular and well-known models of running machines that can be also called electric ones. Motorized treadmills can provide runners with a wide range of features to improve their running experience, so they can benefit from the model's versatility and applicability. It‚Äôs possible to manage the speed and incline with just one touch of a button on the console or using a remote control. As usual, such treadmills are equipped with displays that enable to use of built-in training programs making this equipment highly customized. Such treadmills can provide endless opportunities to diversify your running workout and keep you highly motivated.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510338794" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510338794"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Folding</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681942951218" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681942951218" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>These treadmills are versatile and can come with various features like motorized ones, so there‚Äôs no big difference between them. The obvious spec is that you can fold it easily to store it in the upright position in the closet or even under the bed, by leaving enough space in the room. Folding treadmills are equipped with special folding systems that enable you to raise and lower the deck effortlessly.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510348166" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510348166"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">5. <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/blogs/reviews/best-under-desk-treadmills" class="" target="_blank">Under-Desk</a> Treadmill</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681942976336" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681942976336" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>For those who have no sufficient time to attend the gym and sit for a long time at work, this type of treadmill can be a great solution. The purpose of this gear is to give office workers an opportunity to stay active and fit while working. These tools are much slimmer than the rest models, and have no handrails and display, but can have a small backlit console showing the key metrics. Thus, it‚Äôs easy to place such a treadmill under the working desk and keep walking when you‚Äôre in the office.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681471413697" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1681471413697" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/cf0b043e-a1f9-489a-9c23-de3134c5c664/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/types-of-treadmills.jpg" alt="types of treadmills" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="1040" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="types of treadmills" natural-width="1200" natural-height="1040"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680818727759" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1680818727759" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">Compact Treadmill Benefits</h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1680818742115" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1680818742115" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>When deciding to purchase a treadmill, everyone considers their personal preferences and desires to pick up a good model. Mostly, the choice is based on the features that they can‚Äôt get from running outdoors. For someone, a treadmill can offer a better workout with higher intensity and diversity of running modes they can switch during the training easily and try all of them. Some want to experience more interactive running or arrange some recovery sessions. Nevertheless, we gathered the most obvious pros of compact treadmills you‚Äôll definitely share with us.</p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696609990064" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696609990064" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;"><span style="color: rgb(221, 51, 51);">Our expert <a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/jacek-szymanowski" class="" target="_blank">Jacek Szymanowski</a> told us his own benefits from using a compact treadmill:</span></span><br></span></p><p><span style="font-style: italic;">"<b>Compact treadmill is an amazing piece of equipment to get your steps or some easy run when can‚Äôt go outside (lockdown, bad weather) however if you‚Äôre looking for something that will support your interval work with higher intensities - look somewhere else üòâ.</b></span><span style="font-style: italic;">"</span></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663340399257" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1663340399257"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">‚úÖ All-Round Health Improvement</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1663340399261" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1663340399261" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Having a compact treadmill brings many positive changes to your lifestyle and well-being. With an everyday running session, you‚Äôll succeed in improving your general wellness, staying fit, burning more calories, and losing weight compared to the constant <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/36270758/" class="" target="_blank">sedentary position</a> because of working duties. You can take a compact treadmill and simply put it under the working desk and have some walking without being distracted from your tasks. This option makes a treadmill useful fitness equipment for office workers.</p><p>It‚Äôs a great way to train your heart muscle and pump up your cardiovascular system while improving blood circulation. Alongside this, you'll be able to <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/32970641/" class="" target="_blank">promote your mental health</a> greatly. Although the most important point is that a 30-minute treadmill running session enables you to burn 200-500 calories depending on your weight and height, and training intensity.</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681471462269" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1681471462269" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/c82ada03-ccc4-4252-9341-3fbaf8a30053/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/athlete-treadmill-exercise.jpg" alt="athlete treadmill exercise" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="athlete treadmill exercise" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681435922056" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681435922056" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">‚úÖ A Low-Impact Cardio Workout</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681435932886" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681435932886" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Treadmill running ensures your knees and joints' safety due to the applied cushioning and shock-absorption technologies used to build a reliable belt surface and upgrade its functionality. You can have a minor impact while running on the treadmill compared to the same workout outdoors.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681435978311" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681435978311" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">‚úÖ A Chance to Customize Your Training</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681435989698" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681435989698" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>You can run your favorite courses, sync with the fitness application and pre-set program to make your running session more diverse. With an option of treadmill interactivity, you can arrange immersive training that encourages you for better results by surpassing your previous data and also comparing them. Additionally, you can make a workout more personalized by challenging different muscles and setting new distance goals.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681436022074" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681436022074" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">‚úÖ Versatility</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681436031075" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681436031075" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>In fact, a compact treadmill can be used to improve your current running performance, or just start your running activity at a moderate pace, or it can even be a fitness equipment for rehabilitation. The majority of compact treadmills have two modes: running and walking. So, you can choose the variant that suits your intentions and conditioning. It can be a light walk or jog for rehab, moderate interval training, or intensive running as a part of marathon preparation.</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681949417107" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1681949417107" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/35f80b69-1101-4f5e-99b3-a5465cd339a6/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/female-treadmill-running.jpg" alt="female treadmill running" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="female treadmill running" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681436172897" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1681436172897" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">What to Look For in the Best Compact Treadmill?</span></font></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681436192974" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681436192974" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Pay attention to the following aspects when selecting a fitting compact treadmill to choose the model that will fully cover your needs and even surpass your expectations.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943449925" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943449925"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Speed Range Adjustment</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943420305" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943420305" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Speed setup influences your workout intensity. Some compact treadmills offer a maximum of 5 or 7 mph of the speed range, others come only with 3 mph. There are also 2 in 1 running machines with the possibility to switch between the walking and running modes. So, when choosing a compact treadmill, consider your running style, average stride length, pace, and generally what training mode you like most. Maybe, a 3 mph speed won‚Äôt be enough for you since you plan to do intensive running.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943497161" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943497161"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Dimensions</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943501371" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943501371" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Before purchasing a folding or compact treadmill, you should know how much space you have to store it and keep it folded for running training. Generally, such gear comes in smaller sizes than standard commercial treadmills, although it‚Äôs better to get assured that you have enough living space to spare.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943521587" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943521587"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Additional Features</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943525649" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943525649" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The possibility of spicing up your workout also can‚Äôt be underestimated because it plays an important role in making your progress in running stable and gradual. Due to extra perks like app compatibility, tracking your performance metrics, incline option, pulse sensors availability, etc., you‚Äôll know more about your fitness level, and capabilities, and will find ways to improve it. That‚Äôs why pay attention to incline capabilities. It can be adjusted manually or automatically via remote control or just press the needed buttons on the console. This way, you‚Äôll make your running more challenging and engaging.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943545808" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943545808"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. The Length of the Running Surface</h3></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943552187" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943552187" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The running surface or a belt length is connected directly with the treadmill speed range and an athlete‚Äôs height. That means a higher runner requires a longer treadmill belt and a shorter athlete needs a shorter model. For better comfort choose those running gears with at least 45‚Äù length: such treadmills fit well for dynamic warming up and running. But, if you plan to walk or jog, the running belt 40-42‚Äù long will be enough for you.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943588165" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943588165"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">5. Motor Capacity</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943593232" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943593232" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>When picking up a treadmill, you may notice two options: motor HP, known as motor peak horsepower, and CHP which is continuous horsepower. Unlike peak horsepower which is a treadmill's maximum power, continuous horsepower shows the consistently maintained power a gear can keep during the dynamic running session. The higher CHP a treadmill has, the faster you will run. The stronger a motor is, the more weight it can handle. Therefore, if you plan to walk only, 2.5 HP will be enough, but for running you need at least 3 HP, so the treadmill will be able to withstand all the tension.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510401241" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510401241"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">6. Adjustability</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510406886" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510406886" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>This is non-negotiable because you need a treadmill that adjusts to your fitness goals and the workouts you want to do. Look for something that has an adjustable incline so you can vary the intensity and the type of terrain.</p></div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1696510898035" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1696510898035" data-row-gap="0px" data-extraclass=""><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-12 gf_col-md-12 gf_col-sm-12 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686320640542" data-id="1686320640542"><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1696510898114" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1696510898114" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="8+4" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-8" id="c-1686566620521" data-id="1686566620521"><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510897999" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1696510897999"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><b>Tips From the Champ</b></h2></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-xs-4" id="c-1686566621695" data-id="1686566621695"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510897972" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1696510897972" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-right-lg gf-elm-right-md gf-elm-right-sm gf-elm-right-xs" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/d583efb1-a2f6-4d53-8a26-d6ddafaa60fd/7350738.png" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="512" height="512" data-width="50%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="512" natural-height="512"></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510897985" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510897985"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc="">When choosing a new compact treadmill for your home gym, make sure to keep your priorities straight; you want a sturdy frame, a reliable motor, and a foldable design. Choose a model with a control panel that‚Äôs easy to use and makes workout adjustments seamless. If you‚Äôre looking for something extra durable, find a treadmill with a thicker belt made of high-quality materials. Make sure it has an emergency stop mechanism and non-slip handles.</div></div><div data-label="Row" data-key="row" data-atomgroup="row" id="r-1696510898011" class="gf_row gf_row-gap-0" data-icon="gpicon-row" data-id="1696510898011" data-layout-lg="6+6" data-extraclass="" data-layout-md="6+6" data-layout-sm="6+6" data-layout-xs="12+12" data-row-gap="0px"><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564763470" data-id="1686564763470"><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510898066" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1696510898066" data-resolution="3000x3000"><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-exc=""><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" target="_blank"><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/fc0a1a19-2e31-4fa8-a43b-9c408a123923/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/Oleksiy.jpg" alt="" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="531" height="533" data-width="20%" data-height="auto" title="" natural-width="531" natural-height="533"></a></div></div></div><div class="gf_column gf_col-md-6 gf_col-sm-6 gf_col-lg-6 gf_col-xs-12" id="c-1686564765807" data-id="1686564765807"><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510897977" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510897977"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><b><a href="https://torokhtiy.com/pages/oleksiy-torokhtiy" class="" target="_blank">Oleksiy Torokhtiy</a></b></p></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510898074" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510898074"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf_gs-text-paragraph-1 gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p><span style="font-weight: 700;">Olympic Weightlifting&nbsp;</span><span style="font-weight: 700; color: inherit; font-family: inherit; font-size: inherit; text-align: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px;">Champion</span></p></div></div></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510416647" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510416647"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">7. Monitor Functionality</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510432762" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510432762" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The monitor is the display and the controls of a treadmill. High-end treadmills offer an intuitive, user-friendly monitor that offers valuable info (e.g., speed, time, distance, incline, calories burned) and interactivity (e.g., speed/incline adjustment, fan switch, program selection, heart rate monitoring, etc.) to the user. More advanced monitors might also offer connectivity features such as Bluetooth or compatibility with fitness apps. If you‚Äôre someone who prioritizes progression tracking, look for a treadmill with a versatile and feature-rich monitor.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510443125" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510443125"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">8. Portability</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510448708" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510448708" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>This is key if your space is limited or if you plan on moving the treadmill at all. A lot of treadmills have space-saving designs, like foldable frames. Another thing you need to look out for are transportation wheels; they‚Äôll make your life a lot easier if you need to move the treadmill.</p></div></div><div data-label="Liquid" data-key="liquid" data-atomgroup="module" id="m-1696542894373" class="module-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-liquid" data-ver="1.1" data-id="1696542894373" data-name="Right click on this, and choose Edit Code."><div class="module gf_module- gf_module--lg gf_module--md gf_mo