: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222; text-align: center;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;59.5&quot;}">Consider your running style, stride length, pace and preferred training mode. Some compact treadmills offer speeds of 3, 5 or 7 mph. Some are 2-in-1 and have walking and running modes.</td></tr><tr style="height: 35px;"><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Sunny Easy Assembly&quot;}"><strong>Dimensions</strong></td><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7 #cccccc; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222; text-align: center;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:3,&quot;3&quot;:58.5}">Measure the space you have available for storage and usage.</td></tr><tr style="height: 21px;"><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;"><strong>Additional Features</strong></td><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7 #cccccc; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222; text-align: center;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:3,&quot;3&quot;:58}">Improve your workout with things like app compatibility, performance tracking, incline options, pulse sensors, etc.</td></tr><tr style="height: 21px;"><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;"><strong>Running Surface Length</strong></td><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7 #cccccc; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222; text-align: center;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:3,&quot;3&quot;:57}">Choose according to your height and activity.</td></tr><tr style="height: 21px;"><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;"><strong>Motor Capacity</strong></td><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7 #cccccc; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222; text-align: center;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:3,&quot;3&quot;:57}">HP shows peak power and CHP is sustained power during running. The higher the CHP, the faster you‚Äôll run.</td></tr><tr style="height: 38px;"><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;XTERRA&quot;}"><strong>Adjustability</strong></td><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7 #cccccc; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222; text-align: center;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;55.5&quot;}">The treadmill should have an adjustable incline.</td></tr><tr style="height: 34px;"><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;Mutrisol&quot;}"><strong>Monitor Functionality</strong></td><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7 #cccccc; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222; text-align: center;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:3,&quot;3&quot;:54.5}">The monitor shows key metrics. Premium models are more interactive, have more features and often offer Bluetooth and app compatibility.</td></tr><tr style="height: 38px;"><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:2,&quot;2&quot;:&quot;DAEYEGIM&quot;}"><strong>Portability</strong></td><td style="border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; border-color: #cccccc #b7b7b7 #b7b7b7 #cccccc; border-image: initial; overflow: hidden; padding: 2px 3px; vertical-align: middle; background-color: #ffffff; font-family: Montserrat; font-size: 14pt; font-weight: normal; white-space: normal; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: #222222; text-align: center;" data-sheets-value="{&quot;1&quot;:3,&quot;3&quot;:54.5}">Look for foldable treadmills that save space. Transportation wheels are also a nice addition.</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943655403" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1681943655403" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">How to Use a Compact Treadmill Right?</span></font></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943634817" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943634817" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>When you pick up a compact treadmill, you should consider particular aspects to make a proper choice and stay satisfied with a purchase. Besides defining your needs and preferences, you should also investigate how to use a treadmill correctly, especially how to launch it for the first time and finally how to start running on it without getting injured.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943629668" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943629668"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Know the Treadmill Specs and Available Modes</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943688478" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943688478" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Make sure that you know how to switch on it after unpacking: read the user manual attentively to know what functionality range is possible. Don't forget to lubricate the tread before you use the machine. Then,  try to launch the console and press the available buttons to get assured that it functions well. Try to adjust the speed and incline.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943707186" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943707186"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Do Some Warm-up Exercises</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943713732" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943713732" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Don't forget to <a href="https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/3849057/" class="" target="_blank">warm up before the running</a> training. This is highly important for those who use a treadmill for the first time and have no prior running experience. Stretching can help you to activate muscles and launch blood circulation, so you won't get accidental strains when stepping on the deck improperly.</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696512480992" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1696512480992" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/25fbf033-4b0a-4df8-b2b7-a8367c186d03/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/treadmill-running-session.jpg" alt="treadmill running session" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="treadmill running session" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943755816" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943755816"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Make First Steps</h3></div></div></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943762414" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943762414" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Now, it's time to step on the treadmill: but, remember not to step on the belt when it starts moving. It's recommended to step on the sides of the belt and then step on the running surface. You should start with a minimal speed, so you can easily walk as you walk on the street. Then gradually increase the speed to start jogging, so your body gets accustomed to the tempo and speed.&nbsp;</p><p>Only after you feel that everything is ok and your pace is in unison with the treadmill's speed, you can increase your tempo. You can place your hands in the handrails if they're available for keeping balance.</p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943797759" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943797759"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Listen to Your Body</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1681943803358" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1681943803358" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Don't overtrain, especially if it's your first time using a treadmill. It's better to run at an average pace and speed to get accustomed to such a running mode and a treadmill itself. Like in the beginning, finish the training gradually by slowing the speed down by step to avoid injury. Do cooling down exercises by stretching your body, particularly focusing on lengthening your glute muscles, hamstrings, and calves. That will prevent tightness and soreness.</p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696513546453" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1696513546453" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/2d6d1953-aa6c-4cc1-9da3-f05fee2e6756/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/treadmill-cardio-workout.jpg" alt="treadmill cardio workout" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="treadmill cardio workout" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510515166" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1696510515166" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Folding Treadmill vs Under Desk Treadmill</span></font></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510528441" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510528441" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Before making a choice, you need to consider a few things, like fitness goals and space limitations.</p><p>Folding treadmills are great for traditional workouts. They usually have adjustable speed and incline, which is perfect for adjusting the workout to various fitness levels. They‚Äôre also very versatile because you can use them for a lot of different workout types - anywhere from light, relaxing walks to intense running sessions.</p><p>They‚Äôre typically quite bulky, though, and large. Their price can also be rather high, but in a lot of cases, a higher price means more features and higher quality.</p><p>Under desk treadmills, on the other hand, are super compact and they‚Äôre designed to be convenient. You can use them at home or in your office, which is a fantastic way to stay active while you‚Äôre working. With a sedentary lifestyle being so common these days, these types of treadmills can be game-changers.</p><p>One thing to keep in mind is that they usually have limited speed, so even if it has a lot of gears, you won‚Äôt get an actual intense workout out of them. They‚Äôre meant for walking so, while you will be getting some exercise, it won‚Äôt be anything life-changing as far as your fitness goals go.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1697373615830" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1697373615830" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/3225ef8f-216f-4069-b543-35159a6e4457/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/folding-treadmill-vs-under-desk-treadmill.jpg" alt="folding treadmill vs under desk treadmill" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1400" height="950" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="folding treadmill vs under desk treadmill" natural-width="1400" natural-height="950"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510548276" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="2" data-id="1696510548276" style=""><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs gf-elm-left-lg" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h2 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2"><font color="#000000"><span style="caret-color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Treadmill Maintenance</span></font></h2></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510562944" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510562944" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Treadmills are usually pan investment, so you want them to last for as long as possible. Even with warranties included, having a treadmill break is inconvenient at best. At worst, it‚Äôs a pretty decent new expense.&nbsp;</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510598957" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510598957"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">1. Cleaning</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510583609" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510583609" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>You want to make sure to invest some time into maintenance. Check and clean the belt regularly and make sure to remove any kind of dust, buildup or debris from it.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510614458" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510614458"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">2. Lubrication</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510618868" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510618868" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Lubrication is another thing you don‚Äôt want to skip because it minimizes friction and reduces the strain on the motor. When it comes to how often you need to lubricate - check with what the manufacturer says. You should always go by what they recommend.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510634736" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510634736"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">3. Area Around the Treadmill</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510649694" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510649694" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>The area around your treadmill shouldn‚Äôt be too cluttered. This can be a bit of a challenge in a home setting, but if the space around your treadmill is clean, then there‚Äôs a lot less chance of something getting sucked up in the machine‚Äôs internal components.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510671576" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510671576"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">4. Check Bolts and Screws</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510675754" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510675754" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Any bolts or screws need to be nice and tight so, if you see any coming loose, make sure to tighten them as soon as possible. This maintains the treadmill‚Äôs integrity, so do these checks on a regular basis.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Image" data-key="image" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696512488394" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-image" data-ver="1.0" data-id="1696512488394" data-resolution="3000x3000" style=""><div class="elm gf-elm-center gf_elm-left-xs gf-elm-center-md gf-elm-center-sm gf-elm-center-xs gf-elm-center-lg" data-exc=""><img src="https://ucarecdn.com/a1fc92bc-cfdb-4484-b9a3-6adefb679d68/-/format/auto/-/preview/3000x3000/-/quality/lighter/treadmill-training.jpg" alt="treadmill training" class="gf_image" data-gemlang="en" width="1200" height="800" data-width="100%" data-height="auto" title="treadmill training" natural-width="1200" natural-height="800"></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510689270" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510689270"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">5. Check Power Cords</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510698229" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510698229" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Power cords are some of the most important things to check because if they get frayed or damaged, they can be <a href="https://www1.udel.edu/ehs/newsletter/2015/Safety%20Beacon%2015-1.pdf" class="" target="_blank">extremely dangerous</a>. If you see any damage done to the cord, it‚Äôs best to ask a professional to handle it.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510723519" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510723519"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-xs" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><h3 class="gf_gs-text-heading-2">6. Placement</h3></div></div><div data-label="Text Block" data-key="text-block" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696510727893" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-textblock" data-ver="1" data-id="1696510727893" style="display: block;"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-left gf-elm-left-md gf-elm-left-sm gf-elm-left-lg gf-elm-left-xs gf_gs-text-paragraph-1" data-gemlang="en" data-exc=""><p>Another important thing is the placement - your treadmill needs to be placed on a stable, level surface. If it‚Äôs not, you‚Äôll notice very uneven wear on the belt.</p><p>You may notice that there isn‚Äôt any specific advice regarding exactly how often you need to maintain your treadmill, and there‚Äôs a reason for it; only the manufacturer can give you a schedule and recommend what to check, when and how. But if you‚Äôre ever unsure and you can‚Äôt get in touch with the manufacturer's customer service, you can always ask a professional to help. <a href="https://www.livescience.com/treadmill-benefits" class="" target="_blank">The treadmill can give you a fantastic workout</a>, but only if you keep it in shape.</p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p><p></p></div></div><div data-label="Heading" data-key="heading" data-atomgroup="element" id="e-1696590428466" class="element-wrap" data-icon="gpicon-heading" data-ver="1" data-id="1696590428466"><div class="elm text-edit gf-elm-center gf-elm-left-